<paragraph blockId="22.[144,264,299,323]" box="[144,264,299,323]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">
<emphasis box="[144,264,299,323]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[144,966,338,363]" box="[144,966,338,363]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">This species is named for the yellowish pruinosity on its abdominal terga.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[144,198,432,455]" box="[144,198,432,455]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">
<emphasis box="[144,198,432,455]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">Host</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[144,266,470,494]" box="[144,266,470,494]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[144,242,563,587]" box="[144,242,563,587]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">
<emphasis box="[144,242,563,587]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[144,1101,603,691]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">
This species is very similar to the Chinese species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chao and Liang" authorityName="Chao and Liang" box="[724,1050,603,627]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Exorista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penicilla">
<emphasis box="[724,742,604,627]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[758,850,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1186">penicilla</emphasis>
Chao and Liang
</taxonomicName>
, but is easily distinguished from it by the yellowish pruinosity of the fourth and fifth abdominal terga.
</paragraph>
